.ddx/beads.jsonl:2:{"acceptance":"1. Package cli/internal/ddxroot exists with `Path(ctx, projectRoot) string`.\n2. TestDDxRoot_InTreeMode asserts Path returns \u003cprojectRoot\u003e/.ddx when that dir exists.\n3. TestDDxRoot_ConventionMode_XDGPath asserts Path returns ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/projects/github.com/easel/ddx for a project without .ddx/ and with `git remote get-url origin = git@github.com:easel/ddx.git`.\n4. TestDDxRoot_ConventionMode_LocalFallback covers the no-remote `local/\u003cbasename\u003e-\u003csha\u003e/` form.\n5. TestDDxRoot_URLParsing covers https, ssh, custom-host, missing-remote cases (table-driven).\n6. TestDDxRoot_BootstrapInitsGitRepoInXDG asserts the XDG dir is created with `git init` on first bootstrap and a HEAD commit exists.\n7. TestDDxRoot_BootstrapIdempotent asserts two concurrent calls do not race-create.\n8. TestWorktreeRegistry_FirstWorktreeIsMaster asserts auto-master on first access.\n9. TestWorktreeRegistry_SubsequentRegisterNonMaster asserts later worktrees register but do not overwrite master.\n10. TestWorktreeRegistry_OperatorRePin asserts `ddx project worktree master \u003cpath\u003e` updates the pin.\n11. Static check via lefthook: `rg 'filepath\\.Join\\([^)]*\"\\.ddx\"' cli/ --type go | grep -v '^cli/internal/ddxroot/'` returns zero hits. The lint rule is wired into pre-commit.\n12. Specs listed under SPEC IMPACT are updated in the same commit as the code refactor. Each updated spec references this bead ID.\n13. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... -count=1 green. Existing tests pass without modification.\n14. lefthook run pre-commit passes (including the new no-hardcoded-.ddx-paths rule).","closing_commit_sha":"0826fac9fb709179b22a74b24cf9108623b7ef20","created_at":"2026-05-15T01:16:44.121242708Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-06cbaa90","depends_on_id":"ddx-77eb084e","type":"depends_on","created_at":"2026-05-15T01:33:22Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-06cbaa90","depends_on_id":"ddx-5cc92777","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-15T07:58:30Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM (Principle 1 of epic ddx-602ae31a)\n\nEliminate hardcoded .ddx/ paths so that DDx state anchors correctly regardless of whether the project has a .ddx/ folder. Today every code path joins filepath.Join(projectRoot, \".ddx\", ...) directly, so introducing an XDG fallback or any other root strategy means a many-callsite rewrite.\n\nDESIGN\n\nddxroot.Path(ctx, projectRoot) is the single accessor. It returns:\n- \u003cprojectRoot\u003e/.ddx — when that directory exists (in-tree mode)\n- ${XDG_DATA_HOME}/ddx/projects/\u003chost\u003e/\u003cowner\u003e/\u003crepo\u003e/ — otherwise (convention mode)\n\nProject identity in convention mode is parsed from `git remote get-url origin`:\n- https://github.com/easel/ddx.git → github.com/easel/ddx\n- git@github.com:easel/ddx.git → github.com/easel/ddx\n- https://gitlab.example.com/team/repo → gitlab.example.com/team/repo\n- Local (no remote) → local/\u003cbasename\u003e-\u003cshort-hash-of-abs-path\u003e\n\nThe XDG project directory IS a git repository — `git init`ed on first bootstrap. All DDx state for that project (beads.jsonl, attachments, archive, plugins, etc.) lives there and is versioned. Operators can `git remote add` it to a server to share state with teammates.\n\nWORKTREE REGISTRY (required, not speculative)\n\nEach XDG project root maintains \u003cxdg\u003e/worktrees.json:\n\n  {\"paths\": [{\"path\": \"/Users/erik/Projects/ddx\", \"first_seen_at\": \"...\", \"last_seen_at\": \"...\", \"hostname\": \"...\"}], \"master\": \"/Users/erik/Projects/ddx\"}\n\n- The first worktree to bootstrap an XDG project is auto-marked master.\n- Subsequent worktrees register as non-master.\n- `ddx project worktree list` shows the registry.\n- `ddx project worktree master \u003cpath\u003e` re-pins.\n- Audit log entries (bead events with result_rev/base_rev) include the master path so downstream tools resolve commit SHAs to a known worktree.\n\nDDX_ROOT NEVER PUNNED — bootstrap is atomic, idempotent, and a no-op when the directory already exists. Two concurrent ddx invocations on the same project must not race-create or race-write worktrees.json. Use file-locking (existing gitlock pattern from ddx-6a518fd9) where needed.\n\nAUDIT — every Go file in cli/ that contains the literal \".ddx\" as a path segment must route through ddxroot.Path. Touched packages at minimum:\n- cli/cmd/ (every command that reads/writes state)\n- cli/internal/agent/ (execute_bead*, work/, escalation/)\n- cli/internal/bead/ (store, migrate, lifecycle)\n- cli/internal/server/ (workers, federation, GraphQL adapters)\n- cli/internal/config/ (resolved, types)\n- cli/internal/triage/, cli/internal/metaprompt/, cli/internal/registry/\n- library/checks/ (where ddx-side paths exist)\n\nA regression linter (lefthook hook or go vet analyzer) blocks any PR that introduces a new filepath.Join(..., \".ddx\", ...) literal outside cli/internal/ddxroot/.\n\nSPEC IMPACT — the following docs reference .ddx/ paths and must be updated in this bead:\n- docs/helix/02-design/technical-designs/TD-031-bead-state-machine.md (state paths)\n- docs/helix/02-design/solution-designs/SD-019-multi-project-server-topology.md (project identity)\n- docs/helix/02-design/solution-designs/SD-020-multi-machine-coordinator-topology.md (project identity)\n- docs/helix/02-design/adr/ADR-021-operator-prompt-beads-web-write-path.md (operator-prompt paths)\n- docs/helix/02-design/workers-sessions-operator-surface.md (worker status paths)\n- docs/helix/02-design/plan-2026-04-29-artifact-and-run-architecture.md (FEAT-010 runs/)\n\nEach spec update: replace .ddx/\u003cpath\u003e citations with ddxroot.Path()/\u003cpath\u003e AND add a \"project identity\" subsection where applicable referencing this bead.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Skills/personas install strategy (principle 2 — separate bead).\n- Test matrix (separate bead).\n- Migrating today's in-tree ddx-repo to convention mode (out of scope; this repo stays in-tree as the dogfooding canon).\n\nDEPS\nNone. This is the foundational refactor.","events_attachment":"ddx-06cbaa90/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-06cbaa90","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:config","area:refactor","initiative:zero-footprint","kind:refactor","phase:3","principle:ddx-home"],"lifecycle-migrated-at":"2026-07-02T22:52:48Z","lifecycle-migrated-from-status":"closed","lifecycle-migrated-to-status":"closed","needs-human-reason":"operator decision needed. Bead ddx-06cbaa90 fails Step 0 size limits and was already decomposed into ddx-77eb084e, ddx-fa6eedcc, ddx-b2a5aa0f, ddx-e4c3d791, and ddx-d30bc1a0, with follow-up review-finding bead ddx-5cc92777. The remaining parent acceptance contract is not literally satisfiable from the landed child history: the SPEC IMPACT docs now cite ddx-d30bc1a0 rather than ddx-06cbaa90, and the parent wording requiring the spec updates in the same commit as the code refactor cannot be re-proven without rewriting history. Current HEAD also fails `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... -count=1` in TestWorkerReport_DistinguishesCandidateAndLandedRev at cli/internal/server/workers_gates_test.go:384 and :419, so AC 13 cannot be shown green from this execution. child_ids: ddx-77eb084e, ddx-fa6eedcc, ddx-b2a5aa0f, ddx-e4c3d791, ddx-d30bc1a0, ddx-5cc92777 done: verified the existing decomposition and closed child beads; confirmed the six SPEC IMPACT docs reference ddx-d30bc1a0 instead of ddx-06cbaa90; ran `lefthook run pre-commit` successfully in a clean worktree; ran `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... -count=1` and captured the current internal/server failure. follow_up: either retarget the parent closure semantics to the existing child decomposition or file a new focused parent-closure bead that explicitly updates the docs/acceptance narrative without requiring history rewrite. Handle the failing internal/server gate separately before attempting to prove AC 13 on the parent bead.","needs-human-since":"2026-05-15T17:21:21Z","needs-human-source":"ddx work","needs-human-suggested-action":"review and accept, split, block, or cancel this proposed work","needs-human-summary":"no_changes requested operator attention","notes":"Accepted for autonomous drain 2026-06-01: systemic blocker (production-reachability 'failed to start: context canceled') confirmed a downstream symptom of routing-bug watchdog cancellation, fixed in fizeau v0.14.40. Check builds+runs in 8.7s standalone. Operator approved full burn-down.","parent":"ddx-602ae31a","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-c10f4a3b","status":"closed","title":"ddx home: presence-based root resolution + per-project worktree registry","updated_at":"2026-06-08T04:25:18.437752686Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:15:{"acceptance":"1. Add `TestExecutionCleanupManager_ApplyReapsOnlyStaleAttemptProcessGroups` using injected scanner/killer fakes where needed, proving `--apply` terminates only stale DDx-owned attempt process groups.\n2. Add `TestExecutionCleanupManager_ApplyPreservesLiveAndForeignProcessGroups` proving live run-state, live worker sidecar, active registered worktree, other-project processes, and uncertain candidates are preserved with operator-visible warnings when appropriate.\n3. Add `TestExecutionCleanupManager_ApplyTerminatesGracefullyThenBoundedKill` or an equivalent assertion proving the killer uses graceful terminate before bounded kill when a process group remains alive.\n4. Existing process-reaper tests remain green: `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run 'OrphanHarness|Executor|DockerCloneBackend_ProcessGroupCleanup' -count=1` passes.\n5. `cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... -run 'ExecutionCleanupManager_Apply.*Process|ProcessReap|AttemptDescendant|OrphanHarness|Executor|DockerCloneBackend_ProcessGroupCleanup' -count=1` passes.\n6. `lefthook run pre-commit` passes.","created_at":"2026-06-28T00:56:11.27602192Z","description":"PROBLEM\n`ddx cleanup --apply` can delete stale DDx execution files, but it cannot terminate stale DDx-owned attempt-descendant process groups that are provably orphaned. Heavy leftover processes can continue burning CPU or holding ports after their original attempt is gone.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- `cli/internal/agent/execution_cleanup.go:230-527` applies file cleanup for stale temp dirs, worktrees, scratch roots, stale run-state files, evidence dirs, logs, worker dirs, and refs, but contains no safe process-group termination path.\n- `cli/internal/agent/execution_cleanup.go:110-138` has no process reaping counts or warnings in `ExecutionCleanupSummary`, so apply mode cannot report terminated, preserved, blocked, or unsafe process groups.\n- `cli/internal/agent/orphan_harness_reaper.go:82-100` and `cli/internal/agent/orphan_harness_reaper.go:155-168` intentionally gate startup harness reaping on top-level harness names and dead bead lease owners; that does not cover descendant process groups whose harness root has already exited.\n- `cli/internal/agent/executor_unix.go:10-29` sets process group and parent-death attributes for normal harness children, which cleanup can use only when stale ownership and liveness evidence prove the group is DDx-owned and safe to reap.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nExtend execution cleanup apply mode with an injectable process-group killer and conservative stale ownership checks. Apply may terminate only process groups associated with the current project's DDx execution root where run-state cleanup liveness is expired or missing, the recorded owner PID is gone, the worktree is under the current project execution root, and no live worker sidecar or active registered worktree owns it. Preserve live run-state, live worker sidecar, active registered worktree, other-project processes, and any uncertain candidate. Prefer graceful terminate followed by bounded kill where feasible. Surface blocked warnings instead of silently deleting files when a process is detected but cannot be killed safely.\n\nIN-SCOPE FILES\n- `cli/internal/agent/execution_cleanup.go` and adjacent new platform-specific process cleanup files/tests.\n- `cli/internal/workerstatus/*` or `cli/internal/agent/orphan_harness_reaper*` only for reused process-scanning helpers, not broad rewrites.\n- `docs/helix/01-frame/features/FEAT-010-task-execution.md` and `docs/helix/02-design/solution-designs/SD-025-task-execution-lifecycle.md` only if this child changes the documented cleanup contract.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not edit Niflheim.\n- Do not duplicate `ddx-e0de6369`; that bead owns `.ddx/harness-sessions/` scratch ignore/prune behavior.\n- Do not duplicate `ddx-bbea954f`; that bead owns dirty timeout worktree edit preservation before cleanup deletion.\n- Do not replace the existing parent-death/process-group fixes from `ddx-0d7d5f0e`, `ddx-3113d524`, or `ddx-418c3849`.\n- Do not implement a general-purpose port scanner or host process manager. Port conflict recovery here comes only from safely reaping stale DDx-owned attempt process groups.\n- Do not kill processes outside the current project's DDx execution root, processes tied to live run-state/worker liveness, active registered worktrees, or non-DDx user workloads.\n\nGOVERNING ARTIFACTS\n- `spec:FEAT-010`\n- `spec:SD-025`\n\nPARENT AND DEPS\nParent: `ddx-3106674f` (multi-worker reliability and Niflheim local gates).\nDeps: none.","events":[{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"codex\",\"resolved_model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"route_reason\":\"explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable\",\"fallback_chain\":[]}","created_at":"2026-06-28T05:50:40.536844382Z","kind":"routing","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=codex model=gpt-5.4-mini reason=explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260628T044124-933dc737\",\"harness\":\"codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"route_reason\":\"explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable\",\"input_tokens\":16815190,\"output_tokens\":129624,\"total_tokens\":16944814,\"cost_usd\":0,\"duration_ms\":3199535,\"exit_code\":0}","created_at":"2026-06-28T05:50:40.606307593Z","kind":"cost","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"tokens=16944814 model=gpt-5.4-mini"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"actual_harness\":\"codex\",\"actual_model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"actual_power\":0,\"actual_provider\":\"\",\"attempt_id\":\"20260628T044124-933dc737\",\"bead_id\":\"ddx-0f29e87a\",\"estimated_difficulty\":\"\",\"rejected_route_pins\":null,\"requested_power_class\":\"standard\",\"requested_profile\":\"default\",\"routing_intent_degraded\":false,\"routing_intent_note\":\"\",\"routing_intent_source\":\"default\"}","created_at":"2026-06-28T05:50:42.61709467Z","kind":"execution-routing-intent","source":"ddx work","summary":"sou