.ddx/beads.jsonl:35:{"acceptance":"1. 5 fixture beads chosen and listed in .ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/comparison-fixtures.md with: bead ID, base-rev, original closing commit, characterization (trivial/refactor/test/multi-file/docs).\n2. Path A run: each fixture's bead replayed via ddx try (or ddx work --once) on a branch from base-rev~1; outcomes captured.\n3. Path B run: each fixture dispatched via Agent tool with bead's auto-prompt verbatim; outcomes captured.\n4. Path C run: each fixture dispatched via Agent tool with operator hand-curated prompt; outcomes captured.\n5. Per-fixture, per-path measurements table with the 7 named metrics.\n6. Aggregate stats + failure-mode distribution.\n7. Hypothesis verdict section: H1 / H2 / both / inconclusive.\n8. Recommendations section: which path for which bead-shape.\n9. Report committed at .ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/ddx-vs-subagent-comparison-2026-05-03.md.\n10. Conventional commit ending [\u003cthis-bead-id\u003e].\n11. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n\nDEPS (gate execution; bead stays open until these close): refactor children C4-C13 (ddx-358f2457, ddx-c8f79963, ddx-b669bb9f, ddx-06eb05d8, ddx-848069a3, ddx-9228a484, ddx-0b8780db, ddx-c670ef0a, ddx-387a0178).","created_at":"2026-05-03T19:55:41.880567652Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-31f745cd","depends_on_id":"ddx-358f2457","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-03T19:55:42Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-31f745cd","depends_on_id":"ddx-06eb05d8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-03T19:55:42Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-31f745cd","depends_on_id":"ddx-848069a3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-03T19:55:42Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-31f745cd","depends_on_id":"ddx-0b8780db","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-03T19:55:42Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-31f745cd","depends_on_id":"ddx-387a0178","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-03T19:55:42Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-31f745cd","depends_on_id":"ddx-7e1fed08","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-07T16:13:04Z"}],"description":"Hand-curated sub-agent prompts have been outperforming ddx work / ddx try in this session. Two competing hypotheses for why:\nH1: ddx execution machinery (the 9 fail-prone layers) is unreliable — failure is in the workers/server code.\nH2: Bead authoring quality is insufficient — beads punt investigation; hand-curation papers over the gap.\n\nBoth are plausible. Determining the relative contribution requires a 3-path study, NOT the original 2-path proposal.\n\nTHREE PATHS\n\nPath A: ddx try / ddx work with the bead's auto-prompt verbatim (current production path).\nPath B: Sub-agent dispatched with the bead's auto-prompt verbatim (NOT hand-curated). Same prompt as A; different executor. Isolates ddx machinery from prompt quality.\nPath C: Sub-agent dispatched with operator hand-curated prompt (file:line cites, named tests, explicit non-scope, etc.). Establishes the ceiling.\n\nINTERPRETATION\n- A vs B differ → ddx machinery is the failure (file follow-ups against the 9 layers).\n- B vs C differ → bead authoring quality is the failure (already covered by bead-quality-audit + retrofit).\n- A == B \u003c\u003c C → both are real, with bead quality being the dominant gap.\n\nMETHOD\nPick 5 representative CLOSED beads as fixtures: one trivial fix, one refactor child, one test addition, one multi-file feature, one documentation update. For each fixture, run all 3 paths on a branch from the bead's base-rev (parent of the original work commit). Throwaway commits — the original work is already in main. We're measuring path properties, not producing mergeable code.\n\nMEASUREMENTS\nPer path per bead:\n- Time-to-first-claim (A) / time-to-first-output (B,C)\n- Time-to-merge-eligible-commit (whether or not we merge)\n- Attempts (A) / iterations (B,C)\n- Status outcomes: success / no_changes / preserved / blocked / errored\n- Cost: tokens, USD\n- Manual interventions\n- Failure mode classified per the 9-layer machinery list\n\nOUTPUT\n.ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/ddx-vs-subagent-comparison-2026-05-03.md with:\n- Per-bead per-path table\n- Aggregate stats (median + p99)\n- Failure-mode distribution\n- Hypothesis verdict (H1 vs H2 vs both)\n- Recommendations for which path is appropriate for which bead-shape\n\nTIMING\nThis study runs AFTER the executeloop refactor (C0-C13) lands so the ddx machinery is its post-refactor shape. Running pre-refactor measures behavior we're about to change. RELIABILITY-PRINCIPLES + bead-quality-audit + retrofit + refactor must all complete first. This bead is filed now and EXECUTION DEFERRED.\n\nNOT IN SCOPE\n- Fixing whatever the study reveals (separate bug beads filed from the study's findings)\n- Running against pre-refactor ddx machinery (data we won't act on)\n- Comparing different sub-agent harnesses (different concern)\n\nEVIDENCE\n- ddx-f339c399 documents the 2026-05-04 ddx try ddx-29058e2a --harness=codex no_changes outcome and is partial Path B-vs-C data favoring the bead-quality hypothesis.","events":[{"actor":"ddx bead doctor","body":"dependencies→removed dangling ddx-b669bb9f (1 edge(s))\ndependencies→removed dangling ddx-c670ef0a (1 edge(s))\ndependencies→removed dangling ddx-c8f79963 (1 edge(s))","created_at":"2026-06-08T04:25:18.441797095Z","kind":"repair","source":"ddx bead doctor --fix","summary":"doctor repair applied: 3 change(s)"}],"id":"ddx-31f745cd","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:agent","area:tooling","bead-quality","kind:study","phase:2","reliability"],"notes":"Partial Path B-vs-C evidence: ddx-f339c399 documents the 2026-05-04 ddx try ddx-29058e2a --harness=codex no_changes outcome, supporting the bead-quality hypothesis side of the study.","parent":"ddx-e34994e2","priority":2,"schema_version":1,"status":"open","title":"study: 3-path execution comparison (ddx work vs sub-agent + verbatim bead vs sub-agent + hand-curated)","updated_at":"2026-06-08T04:25:18.441797095Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:39:{"acceptance":"1. library/skills/ddx/SKILL.md \"How this skill works\" section documents global vs project install and references ddx-937de9fc.\n2. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... ./internal/config/... ./internal/registry/... green.\n3. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","created_at":"2026-07-02T18:52:15.649121822Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-43b6b5fe is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 4 of 4 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nPROBLEM\nThe two principles of epic ddx-602ae31a (ddx home resolution + skills/personas install topology) must behave identically across both modes (in-tree and convention). Today there is no single test suite that drives the same scenarios through both modes; coverage is per-mode-ad-hoc and divergence between modes is invisible until operators hit it in production.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nThe two parent beads (ddx-06cbaa90 and ddx-937de9fc) each carry per-feature tests. Neither owns the cross-mode equivalence guarantee.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n\n1. Add cli/internal/agent/test_mode_matrix_test.go (or equivalent suite under a new package) that parameterizes every behaviour-equivalence scenario across both modes:\n\n  for mode in [Convention, InTree]:\n    setup_fixture(mode)\n    for scenario in [\n      \"bead-lifecycle\":           create/show/update/close\n      \"bead-execution\":           ddx try a bead, observe attempt evidence and state mutation\n      \"plugin-skill-resolution\":  ddx-side plugin lookup honors precedence; agent-tier symlinks resolve to plugin content\n      \"persona-binding\":          role → persona resolves correctly per binding config\n      \"worker-drain\":             ddx work --watch picks beads and lands them\n      \"meta-prompt-sync\":         CLAUDE.md (or equivalent) gets the right content\n      \"auto-commit-routing\":      bead create/update auto-commit lands in the right git repo (project's vs XDG's)\n      \"attachments\":              per-attempt event files written to the right anchor\n      \"index-lock-recovery\":      gitlock recovery fires correctly in both modes\n    ]:\n      run scenario in current mode\n      assert behaviour identical to the other mode modulo storage path\n\n2. Fixture setup must be deterministic and isolated:\n   - Convention mode fixture: tempdir as project root, no .ddx/; XDG_DATA_HOME pointed at a per-test tempdir; git remote set to a deterministic URL.\n   - In-tree mode fixture: tempdir as project root WITH .ddx/ pre-created; XDG_DATA_HOME pointed elsewhere (must not be consulted).\n   - Two clones of the same project share an XDG dir — explicitly tested as a separate sub-scenario.\n\n3. Document the test-mode invariant in cli/internal/agent/test_mode_matrix_test.go's package doc: \"Any behavior that diverges between Convention and InTree modes (other than the on-disk anchor) is a regression.\"\n\n4. SPEC UPDATES — propagate the resolver/mode m\n...[truncated]\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- library/skills/ddx/SKILL.md \"How this skill works\" section documents global vs project install and references ddx-937de9fc.\n- cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... ./internal/config/... ./internal/registry/... green.\n- lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.","events":[{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"codex\",\"resolved_model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"route_reason\":\"explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable\",\"fallback_chain\":[]}","created_at":"2026-07-02T23:03:42.34878519Z","kind":"routing","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=codex model=gpt-5.4-mini reason=explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260702T221915-ece25de1\",\"harness\":\"codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"route_reason\":\"