.ddx/beads.jsonl:49:{"acceptance":"1. A Go test in cli/internal/agent/ reproduces an attempt whose candidate commit would be rewritten after the first commit and asserts it is prevented or reconciled (candidate preserved), NOT discarded-and-rerun. 2. Existing land/divergence tests still pass. 3. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... passes; go build ./... succeeds.","created_at":"2026-06-28T03:08:04.1203069Z","description":"PROBLEM\nAgents keep tripping the execute-bead one-commit/no-amend contract (the implementation commit is rewritten/amended/rebased after the first commit). Today this is DETECTED post-hoc and the whole attempt is discarded and re-run, wasting long, expensive runs (observed 3047s / 15.3M-token attempts thrown away).\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- cli/internal/agent/execute_bead_land.go (divergence/ancestry resolution, ~line 187 and ~910-927): a diverged/rewritten candidate is resolved by aborting the claim (detect-then-fail), not by preventing or correcting the rewrite.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Prevent or auto-correct the contract violation rather than discarding the attempt: e.g. detect a post-first-commit rewrite before land and reconcile it (or instruct/guard the harness to not amend) so a successful candidate is preserved instead of re-run from scratch.\n- This is DISTINCT from the mixed_commit_and_no_changes_rationale detector in execute_bead.go:~1419 (commit+rationale mismatch). Do NOT target that path.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Do not relax the audit-trail rule (never squash/rebase/filter landed attempt history).\n- Do not touch the mixed_commit detector.\n- Do not change Fizeau routing.\n\nPROVENANCE\nDerived from a session-harvest of local Claude/Codex operator prompts (2026-06-27), classified into deficiency-papering vs intent, then put through two adversarial-review rounds that dropped every item already shipped. This item survived as a verified, non-redundant gap. See docs/session-harvest-playbook.md.","id":"ddx-3c865b16","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:agent","area:execute-bead","kind:reliability","source:session-harvest-2026-06-27"],"priority":2,"schema_version":1,"status":"open","title":"Make execute-bead auto-comply with the one-commit/no-amend contract","updated_at":"2026-06-28T03:08:04.1203069Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:53:{"acceptance":"1. cli/internal/agent/test_mode_matrix_test.go (or a comparable suite) exists, parameterized over [Convention, InTree] modes and the nine listed scenarios.\n2. The suite passes for every (mode, scenario) cell.\n3. TestModeMatrix_TwoClonesShareXDG asserts two project worktrees pointing at the same git remote share the XDG project dir AND register both in worktrees.json with one auto-pinned as master.\n4. TestModeMatrix_OperatorExpectationDocumented asserts the suite's package godoc clearly states the cross-mode equivalence invariant.\n5. Every spec listed under SPEC UPDATES has a citation to ddx-06cbaa90 or ddx-937de9fc (verified by `rg \"ddx-06cbaa90|ddx-937de9fc\" docs/helix/`).\n6. CLAUDE.md \"Persona System\" section updated to document install precedence and references ddx-937de9fc.\n7. library/skills/ddx/SKILL.md \"How this skill works\" section documents global vs project install and references ddx-937de9fc.\n8. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/agent/... ./cmd/... ./internal/config/... ./internal/registry/... green.\n9. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","created_at":"2026-05-15T01:18:04.1850481Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-43b6b5fe","depends_on_id":"ddx-06cbaa90","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-15T01:18:10Z"},{"issue_id":"ddx-43b6b5fe","depends_on_id":"ddx-937de9fc","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-15T01:18:10Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nThe two principles of epic ddx-602ae31a (ddx home resolution + skills/personas install topology) must behave identically across both modes (in-tree and convention). Today there is no single test suite that drives the same scenarios through both modes; coverage is per-mode-ad-hoc and divergence between modes is invisible until operators hit it in production.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nThe two parent beads (ddx-06cbaa90 and ddx-937de9fc) each carry per-feature tests. Neither owns the cross-mode equivalence guarantee.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n\n1. Add cli/internal/agent/test_mode_matrix_test.go (or equivalent suite under a new package) that parameterizes every behaviour-equivalence scenario across both modes:\n\n  for mode in [Convention, InTree]:\n    setup_fixture(mode)\n    for scenario in [\n      \"bead-lifecycle\":           create/show/update/close\n      \"bead-execution\":           ddx try a bead, observe attempt evidence and state mutation\n      \"plugin-skill-resolution\":  ddx-side plugin lookup honors precedence; agent-tier symlinks resolve to plugin content\n      \"persona-binding\":          role → persona resolves correctly per binding config\n      \"worker-drain\":             ddx work --watch picks beads and lands them\n      \"meta-prompt-sync\":         CLAUDE.md (or equivalent) gets the right content\n      \"auto-commit-routing\":      bead create/update auto-commit lands in the right git repo (project's vs XDG's)\n      \"attachments\":              per-attempt event files written to the right anchor\n      \"index-lock-recovery\":      gitlock recovery fires correctly in both modes\n    ]:\n      run scenario in current mode\n      assert behaviour identical to the other mode modulo storage path\n\n2. Fixture setup must be deterministic and isolated:\n   - Convention mode fixture: tempdir as project root, no .ddx/; XDG_DATA_HOME pointed at a per-test tempdir; git remote set to a deterministic URL.\n   - In-tree mode fixture: tempdir as project root WITH .ddx/ pre-created; XDG_DATA_HOME pointed elsewhere (must not be consulted).\n   - Two clones of the same project share an XDG dir — explicitly tested as a separate sub-scenario.\n\n3. Document the test-mode invariant in cli/internal/agent/test_mode_matrix_test.go's package doc: \"Any behavior that diverges between Convention and InTree modes (other than the on-disk anchor) is a regression.\"\n\n4. SPEC UPDATES — propagate the resolver/mode model to every doc that references .ddx/ paths or project state. Each spec update added in this bead's commit cites principle-numbered tags so future readers see the link:\n   - TD-031 bead state machine — \"Storage anchors via ddxroot.Path(); see ddx-06cbaa90.\"\n   - SD-019 multi-project-server-topology — Project identity from `host/owner/repo`; reference ddx-06cbaa90.\n   - SD-020 multi-machine-coordinator-topology — same.\n   - ADR-021 operator-prompt-beads-web-write-path — reference ddx-06cbaa90.\n   - workers-sessions-operator-surface.md — worker status paths through ddxroot.Path().\n   - plan-2026-04-29-artifact-and-run-architecture — FEAT-010 paths through resolver.\n   - library/skills/ddx/SKILL.md and CLAUDE.md — install precedence per ddx-937de9fc.\n   - library/README.md — install topology overview.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- New behaviours (every scenario in the matrix is already covered by ddx-06cbaa90 or ddx-937de9fc per-feature tests; this is the cross-mode equivalence layer).\n- Migration tooling for existing in-tree repos (out of scope; this repo stays in-tree).\n\nDEPS\nddx-06cbaa90 (ddx home resolution).\nddx-937de9fc (skills/personas/plugins).","events":[{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"codex\",\"resolved_model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"route_reason\":\"explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable\",\"fallback_chain\":[]}","created_at":"2026-07-02T18:44:09.492671799Z","kind":"routing","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=codex model=gpt-5.4-mini reason=explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260702T182331-2f12c63c\",\"harness\":\"codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"route_reason\":\"explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable\",\"input_tokens\":4993264,\"output_tokens\":70667,\"total_tokens\":5063931,\"cost_usd\":0,\"duration_ms\":1221229,\"exit_code\":0}","created_at":"2026-07-02T18:44:09.609759531Z","kind":"cost","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"tokens=5063931 model=gpt-5.4-mini"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"actual_harness\":\"codex\",\"actual_model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"actual_power\":0,\"actual_provider\":\"\",\"attempt_id\":\"