.ddx/beads.jsonl:54:{"acceptance":"1. Context typed accessors implemented. Tests: `TestWithIdentity_RoundTrip`, `TestIdentityFromContext_AbsentReturnsFalse`, `TestWithTrace_RoundTrip`.\n2. Foundational sub-interfaces (`BeadInitializer`, `BeadReader`, `BeadLifecycle`, `BeadEventReader`, `BeadEventWriter`) declared with ctx-first signatures. `*Store` satisfies only the non-event foundation interfaces in this bead — compile-time assertions: `var _ BeadInitializer = (*Store)(nil)`, `var _ BeadReader = (*Store)(nil)`, `var _ BeadLifecycle = (*Store)(nil)`. No `BeadEventReader`/`BeadEventWriter` assertion is added until E.\n3. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... passes.\n4. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","created_at":"2026-05-12T20:42:31.004428017Z","description":"PROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-215b08a2 is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 2 of 2 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\nPROBLEM\nParent bead ddx-c6317784 is too broad for one execution pass. This child owns part 2 of 5 of that parent scope.\n\nROOT CAUSE\n# PROBLEM\nThe bead backend interface today (`cli/internal/bead/backend.go`) is JSONL-shaped: `RawBackend` requires whole-corpus `ReadAll`/`WriteAll`, and `Backend` declares only 22 of `*Store`'s 69 public methods. Per TD-027 (the canonical Bead Storage System and Lifecycle spec), the bead architecture needs:\n\n- A typed `Operation` pattern with `Apply(b *Bead) error` (CAS via error returns)\n- 11 LSP-clean storage sub-interfaces composing `Backend`\n- Pluggable `IDGenerator` and parallel `LifecycleSubscriber`\n- `context.Context` first-parameter discipline on every interface method\n- Sentinel errors (`ErrNotFound`, `ErrConflict`, `ErrInvalidID`, `ErrAlreadyClaimed`, `ErrNotClaimedByOwner`, `ErrUnsupported`)\n- The optional `OperationApplier` interface on `RawBackend` so JSONL backends can preserve heartbeat sidecar optimization\n- A canonical Bead data model (field enumeration + invariants + JSONL wire format + schema-versioning policy)\n\nThis bead lays the foundation that all per-concern beads (L/C/E/X/Q/D/A/MIG) depend on. It declares the event reader/writer interfaces but deliberately does not migrate `AppendEvent`, `Events`, or `EventsByKind`; the E bead owns event-method ctx threading and `*Store` event interface satisfaction.\n\n# ROOT CAUSE\n- `cli/internal/bead/backend.go:10-67` — `RawBackend` (4 whole-corpus methods) + `Backend` (22 high-level methods, incomplete).\n- `cli/internal/bead/store.go` — `*Store` exposes 69 public methods, none take `ctx context.Context`.\n- `cli/internal/bead/axon_backend.go:340-381` — `WriteAll` ships entire corpus per mutation (catastrophic for Postgres).\n- Operation pattern, IDGenerator, sentinel errors, context discipline — all absent.\n- Bead data model (the canonical schema of fields + invariants) — only implicit in the Go struct.\n\n# PROPOSED FIX\nImplement TD-027 §5–§13 foundation pieces that are required before the per-concern beads can execute.\n\n## New files\n\n1. `cli/internal/bead/operation.go` — `Operation` interface with `Apply(b *Bead) error`. `MutateFunc` adapter for ad-hoc mutations. Empty named-op section (per-concern beads add their op types).\n2. `cli/internal/bead/id.go` — `ValidateID`, format constants (`DefaultIDPrefix`, `MaxIDLength`, `MinIDLength`), `IDGenerator` int\n...[truncated]\n\nPROPOSED FIX\nImplement only this child acceptance slice:\n- Context typed accessors implemented. Tests: `TestWithIdentity_RoundTrip`, `TestIdentityFromContext_AbsentReturnsFalse`, `TestWithTrace_RoundTrip`.\n- Foundational sub-interfaces (`BeadInitializer`, `BeadReader`, `BeadLifecycle`, `BeadEventReader`, `BeadEventWriter`) declared with ctx-first signatures. `*Store` satisfies only the non-event foundation interfaces in this bead — compile-time assertions: `var _ BeadInitializer = (*Store)(nil)`, `var _ BeadReader = (*Store)(nil)`, `var _ BeadLifecycle = (*Store)(nil)`. No `BeadEventReader`/`BeadEventWriter` assertion is added until E.\n\nNON-SCOPE\nDo not implement parent acceptance criteria assigned to sibling child beads. Preserve every parent non-scope constraint unless this child explicitly narrows it.","events":[{"actor":"erik","body":"{\"decision\":\"warn\",\"decision_source\":\"pre_claim_intake\",\"detail\":\"description drops commitment \\\"cli/internal/bead/axon_backend.go:340\\\"\",\"fingerprint\":\"9a9f3e7563c088c6559b50170a909615619d5996d3af04d242043c3656f19c85\",\"policy_mode\":\"warn-only\",\"reason\":\"rewrite_rejected\",\"rule_id\":\"pre_claim_intake.rewrite_rejected\",\"suggested_action\":\"revise the rewrite so it preserves every explicit commitment\"}","created_at":"2026-05-12T22:18:06.71237507Z","kind":"intake.warn","source":"ddx work","summary":"rewrite_rejected"},{"actor":"erik","body":"{\"rationale\":\"The bead is mostly execution-ready: the description has PROBLEM/ROOT CAUSE/PROPOSED FIX/NON-SCOPE with file:line anchors, AC are numbered and testable, labels are complete, and the prompt is self-contained. Two rubric gaps remain: the title is not imperative/scope-clear, and the bead does not explicitly list deps or state \\\"No deps.\\\"\",\"score\":6,\"suggested_fixes\":[\"Rewrite the title as a one-line imperative that names the subsystem and change, removing the \\\"F (Foundation)\\\" prefix and \\\"part 2\\\" phrasing.\",\"Add an explicit deps field or state \\\"No deps.\\\" in the bead body so dependency status is unambiguous.\"],\"waivers_applied\":[]}","created_at":"2026-05-12T22:18:33.527795972Z","kind":"bead-quality.lint","source":"ddx work","summary":"score=6"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"codex\",\"resolved_model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"fallback_chain\":[],\"requested_harness\":\"codex\",\"requested_model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\"}","created_at":"2026-05-12T22:25:35.365621908Z","kind":"routing","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=codex model=gpt-5.4-mini"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260512T221833-e7b1512b\",\"harness\":\"codex\",\"mod