.ddx/beads.jsonl:60:{"acceptance":"1. Package cli/internal/ddxroot exists with exported Path(ctx, projectRoot) function.\n2. TestDDxRoot_DefaultsToProjectRootDotDDx asserts Path returns filepath.Join(projectRoot, \".ddx\") in the default (no XDG fallback yet) case.\n3. Static check: `rg 'filepath\\.Join\\([^)]*\"\\\\.ddx\"' cli/ --type go | grep -v '^cli/internal/ddxroot/'` returns zero hits. This is the regression guard for the audit. (The check is wired into lefthook as a pre-commit rule.)\n4. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./... -count=1 green. All existing tests pass without modification.\n5. The audit covers at minimum the 12 path-writers enumerated in the description. The bead's no_changes_rationale.txt (if used) MUST list every file modified by the audit, grouped by package.\n6. lefthook run pre-commit passes, including the new \"no-hardcoded-.ddx-paths\" rule.","created_at":"2026-05-15T01:08:53.863138043Z","description":"PROBLEM\nEvery place in the codebase that writes to .ddx/\u003csomething\u003e today hardcodes filepath.Join(projectRoot, \".ddx\", ...). This makes it impossible to relocate the DDx state to an XDG location for convention-mode projects without auditing and rewriting every call site. A leaked path means the convention-mode invariant (\"no files written to project tree without a .ddx/ folder\") breaks the moment that code path runs.\n\nThe full enumeration of touched paths is at minimum:\n- .ddx/config.yaml\n- .ddx/beads.jsonl\n- .ddx/beads-archive.jsonl\n- .ddx/attachments/\u003cid\u003e/\n- .ddx/executions/\u003crun-id\u003e/\n- .ddx/run-state/\u003cid\u003e.json\n- .ddx/metrics/attempts.jsonl\n- .ddx/.git-tracker.lock\n- .ddx/plugins/\u003cname\u003e/\n- .ddx/workers/\u003cid\u003e/\n- .ddx/agent-logs/\n- .ddx/scratch/\n- and likely 10+ more across cli/internal/server/, cli/cmd/, library/checks/, scripts/\n\nROOT CAUSE\nThere is no single accessor that returns \"the DDx root for this project\". cli/internal/config/ has GetMetaPrompt() and similar config getters, but no DDxRoot(ctx) function. Every path-writer reaches into the file system directly.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n1. Add a new package cli/internal/ddxroot with a single public function: `Path(ctx context.Context, projectRoot string) string`. Today returns filepath.Join(projectRoot, \".ddx\"); a follow-up bead (E2) extends it to fall back to XDG when projectRoot/.ddx does not exist.\n2. Audit every Go file in cli/ that contains the literal \".ddx\" as a path segment. Replace `filepath.Join(projectRoot, \".ddx\", ...)` with `filepath.Join(ddxroot.Path(ctx, projectRoot), ...)`. The audit must cover cli/cmd/, cli/internal/, library/checks/ (where applicable to ddx-side paths).\n3. Add a build-time linter check (or a pre-commit hook lint rule) that fails the build if a new `filepath.Join.*\"\\\\.ddx\"` literal appears outside cli/internal/ddxroot/. Use go vet via a custom analyzer OR a simple ripgrep-based pre-commit hook (lefthook).\n4. The resolver MUST NOT change behaviour in this bead: for any projectRoot today, ddxroot.Path returns exactly filepath.Join(projectRoot, \".ddx\"). This bead is a pure refactor — no functional change.\n5. Existing tests must continue to pass without modification. If any test fails, it has hardcoded .ddx in a way that bypassed the resolver — fix that test.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- XDG fallback path (E2 bead).\n- Convention mode bootstrap (E2 bead).\n- `ddx init --global` (E3 bead).\n- Manifest overlay (E5 bead).\n- Migration of existing data (none required; behaviour is identical).\n\nDEPS\nNone. This is the foundational refactor that the rest of the epic builds on.","id":"ddx-564ea1cf","issue_type":"task","labels":["area:config","area:refactor","kind:refactor","phase:3","initiative:zero-footprint"],"notes":"Superseded by epic restructure into 3 consolidated beads aligned to the two principles: (1) bulletproof ddx home resolution, (2) centralized vs in-project skills/personas. New beads pending.","parent":"ddx-602ae31a","priority":1,"schema_version":1,"status":"cancelled","title":"config: DDxRoot resolver + audit every .ddx/ path writer","updated_at":"2026-05-15T01:16:05.219587014Z"}
