.ddx/beads.jsonl:72:{"acceptance":"1. TestAxonBackend_CreateAndGet passes against the GraphQL-backed implementation.\n2. TestAxonBackend_UpdateMutatesAndPersists passes against the GraphQL-backed implementation.\n3. TestAxonBackend_ClaimAndUnclaim passes against the GraphQL-backed implementation.\n4. TestAxonBackend_DepAddRemoveAndTree passes against the GraphQL-backed implementation.\n5. TestAxonBackend_AppendEventSplitsIntoEventsCollection passes and verifies event_of links.\n6. backend_axon.go / axon_backend.go no longer use local JSONL snapshots as the primary storage path when AxonBackend is selected with a GraphQL client.\n7. cd cli \u0026\u0026 go test ./internal/bead/... -run \"TestAxonBackend_CreateAndGet|TestAxonBackend_UpdateMutatesAndPersists|TestAxonBackend_ClaimAndUnclaim|TestAxonBackend_DepAddRemoveAndTree|TestAxonBackend_AppendEventSplitsIntoEventsCollection\" -count=1 passes.\n8. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","archived_at":"2026-05-07T04:29:14Z","closing_commit_sha":"b98d4043ddcf32bb93fa8ac0b0c6912e6442b777","created_at":"2026-05-06T01:45:00.352772945Z","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"ddx-6d5c436e","depends_on_id":"ddx-208a5bee","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-05-06T01:45:01Z"}],"description":"PROBLEM\nAfter the client boundary exists, AxonBackend still needs real GraphQL CRUD, dependency, and event operations. The parent bead currently asks for too many operations at once and has repeatedly produced no_changes_needs_investigation.\n\nROOT CAUSE WITH FILE:LINE\n- cli/internal/bead/axon_backend.go:123 reads from local collection files, not Axon queries.\n- cli/internal/bead/axon_backend.go:175 rewrites local collection files, not Axon mutations.\n- cli/internal/bead/store.go higher-level operations depend on RawBackend ReadAll/WriteAll/WithLock semantics, so the GraphQL backend must preserve store behavior while changing storage transport.\n\nPROPOSED FIX\n- Implement GraphQL-backed Create, Get, Update, Claim/Unclaim, Close, DepAdd, DepRemove, and AppendEvent behavior through the RawBackend integration path.\n- Preserve optimistic/concurrent update expectations from the existing store tests.\n- Keep event history split into ddx_bead_events and linked to bead rows through event_of.\n- Keep local JSONL backend untouched.\n\nNON-SCOPE\n- Backend selection config plumbing.\n- Import/export conformance matrix beyond targeted operation tests.","events_attachment":"ddx-6d5c436e/events.jsonl","id":"ddx-6d5c436e","issue_type":"task","labels":["phase:2","area:beads","area:storage","kind:feature","axon","from:ddx-9c5bca8f"],"lifecycle-migrated-at":"2026-07-02T22:52:48Z","lifecycle-migrated-from-status":"closed","lifecycle-migrated-to-status":"closed","parent":"ddx-9c5bca8f","priority":0,"schema_version":1,"session_id":"eb-f626cc76","spec_id":"TD-030","status":"closed","title":"bead/axon: implement GraphQL-backed CRUD, deps, and events","updated_at":"2026-05-06T08:00:58.245469033Z"}
.ddx/beads.jsonl:74:{"acceptance":"1. New Vitest `cli/internal/server/frontend/src/lib/design-tokens.test.ts`: the resolved Tailwind theme contains NO generic values (no `#8e35a3`, no `#4878c6`, no `#f9fafb`/`#ffffff` surface) and `accent-lever === '#3B5B7A'`; regenerating `design-tokens.json` from DESIGN.md keeps these.\n2. Inter is actually LOADED: a Playwright assertion that `document.fonts` includes Inter (not merely declared) and `getComputedStyle(h1).fontFamily` resolves to the loaded family; re-baseline `cli/internal/server/frontend/e2e/screenshots.spec.ts` snapshots.\n3. The `semanticColors` alias layer is retained (class names unchanged); design:export remains the source of truth.\n4. cd cli/internal/server/frontend \u0026\u0026 bun run test \u0026\u0026 bun run test:e2e green.\n5. lefthook run pre-commit passes.","created_at":"2026-06-05T17:51:32.412466203Z","description":"PROBLEM: Two issues mask the intended design system (`.stitch/DESIGN.md`: warm-paper brutalist). (1) `cli/internal/server/frontend/design-tokens.json` is the STALE generic Stitch export (`tertiary:#8e35a3` purple, `surface:#f9fafb`, Inter for all roles) — its warm palette only reaches the app because `cli/internal/server/frontend/tailwind.config.js:8-37` hardcodes `semanticColors` that override the JSON. So `bun run design:export` regenerates GENERIC values; a reader cannot tell which file is authoritative. (2) The typeface (`Inter`, tailwind.config.js:39-46) is SPECIFIED but never LOADED (no @font-face/@fontsource/Google Fonts anywhere) -\u003e renders the OS system-sans fallback.\n\nROOT CAUSE: the design:export pipeline emits the generic default token DATA (not DESIGN.md's warm palette); and no font asset is imported. Per codex: `semanticColors` is the load-bearing alias layer (KEEP it) — only the generated token DATA is stale. Operator decision: load Inter (do NOT introduce a new display font — that would be a spec change).\n\nPROPOSED FIX: Regenerate `design-tokens.json` from `.stitch/DESIGN.md` (warm palette: #3B5B7A lever-steel, #F4EFE6 cream, etc.) so the export pipeline is the source of truth and carries the correct values; KEEP the `semanticColors` alias layer in tailwind.config.js (do not delete it; ensure it reads the regenerated tokens rather than shadowing stale ones). Add Inter via `@fontsource-variable/inter` (`bun add`), import in `cli/internal/server/frontend/src/app.css`, so all non-mono roles render Inter instead of system fallback.\n\nNON-SCOPE: introducing a distinctive display font (operator chose Inter-only); off-palette utility migration (separate bead); deleting the semanticColors layer.","events":[{"actor":"erik","body":"{\"decision\":\"warn\",\"decision_source\":\"pre_claim_intake\",\"detail\":\"readiness route unavailable: lifecycle dispatch: project root mutation rejected for bead ddx-7202170f (changed existing dirty paths: .ddx/beads.jsonl, .ddx/metrics/locks.jsonl)\",\"fingerprint\":\"c1b4d41b983a7dbd24fbf55edf0c3dea2a6ecf4b29b47a873345379dfa346bf6\",\"policy_mode\":\"warn-only\",\"reason\":\"system_unready\",\"rule_id\":\"pre_claim_intake.system_unready\",\"suggested_action\":\"revise the rewrite so it preserves every explicit commitment\",\"warning_fingerprint\":\"c1b4d41b983a7dbd24fbf55edf0c3dea2a6ecf4b29b47a873345379dfa346bf6\"}","created_at":"2026-06-07T14:11:46.198904091Z","kind":"intake.warn","source":"ddx work","summary":"system_unready"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"resolved_provider\":\"codex\",\"resolved_model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"route_reason\":\"explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable\",\"fallback_chain\":[]}","created_at":"2026-06-07T15:00:36.607644379Z","kind":"routing","source":"legacy agent execute-bead","summary":"provider=codex model=gpt-5.4-mini reason=explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable"},{"actor":"ddx","body":"{\"attempt_id\":\"20260607T141401-5bce5807\",\"harness\":\"codex\",\"model\":\"gpt-5.4-mini\",\"route_reason\":\"explicit_pin_discovery_unavailable\",\"input_tokens\":29687618,\"output_tokens\":941